text: I think it looks pretty darn funny and I think people should wait to judge until they see it...or don't and refrain from judgement because they didn't see it. And I think it's wrong to criticize, as some have, because they feel family guy has suffered as a result of MacFarlane's other ventures. I love family guy but shows don't last forever before what made it so wonderful becomes compromised in some way (aka "Jumping the shark"), not that I'm saying I think Family Guy has gone that way.  However, I've unintentionally missed most episodes as of late, so I can't say one way or the other with any kind of authority.    But, more than all of that, IMHO MacFarlane is an amazing talent and he should be allowed to and encouraged by his fans to try new things and do what makes him happy.  We should all want that for ourselves and for others, because after all, if we're not seeking happiness what the hell are we here for?
